saying goodbye to my Unnies, feels damn heartbreaking.. I discovered BLACKPINK, 4 years ago, and since then, I've been a hardcore BLINK. Personally, for me, BLACKPINK isn't just all about their music; it's them. Its JENNIE unnie, JISOO unnie, ROSÃ‰ unnie and LISA unnie. They are my inspiration, my comfort buddies, my motivators, my mood uplifters, my support system, my life guides, my sisters, my IDOLS. They are a part of who I am. If I'm a strong, self sufficient, independent and HAPPY person today, the credits go to BLACKPINK. They taught me to love myself and be proud of who I am.

Happy 7th Anniversary to BLACKPINK. I'm so proud of my unnies, and I'm so grateful to be a part of this amazing fandom. Proud to be a BLINK.

Thanks for everything BLACKPINK. You were, are, and will forever be my idols. 

XOXO, Luna <3

text: As a supporter of Blackpink since 2016, I'm incredibly proud of all four of you. I knew you would be successful since you were YG's first girl group since 2NE1, but I never expected something like this. I've watched you grow from girls with a strong passion to perform into women with an even stronger passion to perform for your millions of fans. When I stood in that crowd at HYDE park after waiting for so many years and missing every opportunity to see you, I couldn't help but break down. Especially when Boombayah played. I looked around at the huge crowd of hundreds of thousands of people, all there for blackpink. All there for those four humble, fun, charismatic girls that I loved and supported for all these years. author: @Lalilou_b
text:
There are no words to describe how much I love these 4 wonderful girls. They came into my life just when I needed to learn to love myself and believe in my dreams. 
They are so important to me, it's like a family.
I love them so much for everything they do and all they are. I am grateful to have known them for a little over 5 years and I feel lucky to be part of the blinks.
When I think back to those years of following them, watching them grow and become the global stars they are, I am so moved. 
I also realize that they have grown up well and now they look fulfilled and happy with their careers. I wish them every success even though they have already made history. 
I will always remember them as an example of success and work. They are living proof that with determination, talent and hope, we can succeed in making our dreams a reality. 
During these years, I have evolved with them and what I find beautiful is that despite their success and their statue of the biggest girlsband in the world, they remain humble and show us a little more each time who they are : beautiful women inside and outside, full of talent and merit, full of smile and courage. 
I admire them so much to continue to be themselves no matter what. 
I wish them all the happiness in the world and I hope with all my heart that they will continue to follow their dreams and find the peace. 
Jisoo, Jennie, RosÃ©, Lisa, I love you to the moon and back, you're my hope, my hapiness, my family, my safe place et I'll always supporting you, no matter your choises. 
I'm so thankfull you have no idea. 
You are my models, thank you for existing and make my life better â¤ï¸
And I hope that, beyond your phenomenal success, you are happy in your life cause you deserve it so far ğŸ’•

Love you all from my heart and my soul, 

This is a letter, from me to BLACKPINK.

text:
Blackpink (Korean: ë¸”ë™í•‘í¬; RR: Beullaekpingkeu, stylized in all caps or as BLÉ…Ï½KPIĞ˜K) is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment, consisting of members Jisoo, Jennie, RosÃ©, and Lisa. The group debuted in August 2016 with their single album Square One, which featured "Whistle" and "Boombayah", their first number-one entries on South Korea's Gaon Digital Chart and the US Billboard World Digital Song Sales chart, respectively.

Kim Ji-soo (Korean: ê¹€ì§€ìˆ˜; born January 3, 1995), known mononymously as Jisoo, is a South Korean singer and actress. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. Outside of her music career, she made her acting debut with a cameo role in the 2015 series The Producers and played her first leading role in the JTBC series Snowdrop (2021â€“22), for which she won a Seoul International Drama Award.

Jennie Kim (Korean: ê¹€ì œë‹ˆ; born January 16, 1996), known mononymously as Jennie, is a South Korean singer and rapper. Born and raised in South Korea, Jennie studied in New Zealand for five years before returning to South Korea in 2010. She debuted as a member of the girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. In November 2018, Jennie made her debut as a solo artist with the single "Solo". The song was commercially successful, topping both the Gaon Digital Chart and Billboard's World Digital Songs chart. In 2023, she will be making her acting debut in the HBO series The Idol, under the stage name Jennie Ruby Jane.

Roseanne Park (born 11 February 1997), known mononymously as RosÃ© (Korean: ë¡œì œ), is a Korean-New Zealand singer and dancer based in South Korea. Born in New Zealand and raised in Australia, RosÃ© signed with South Korean label YG Entertainment following a successful audition in 2012 and trained for four years before debuting as a member of the girl group Blackpink in August 2016.

Lalisa Manobal (also spelled Manoban; born Pranpriya Manobal; March 27, 1997), known mononymously as Lisa, is a Thai rapper, singer and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, which debuted under YG Entertainment in 2016.
